  "comment_text": {
    "sn15.10:1.1": "This Sutta is also at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/iti17/en/sujato'>Iti 17</a> and [iti]18(). ",
    "sn15.10:2.2": "Mount Vepulla (“huge”; modern Vipula) lies immediately north of the Vulture’s Peak. It was probably visible to the Buddha, hence he used the proximate pronoun <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ima</i> (“this”). Today it is crowned with a Jain temple. Its past names are given at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn15.20/en/sujato'>SN 15.20</a>. ",
