  "root_text": {
    "sn15.10:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 15.10 ",
    "sn15.10:0.2": "1. Paṭhamavagga ",
    "sn15.10:0.3": "Puggalasutta ",
    "sn15.10:1.1": "Ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate. ",
    "sn15.10:1.2": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
    "sn15.10:1.3": "“bhikkhavo”ti. ",
    "sn15.10:1.4": "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṁ. ",
    "sn15.10:1.5": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
    "sn15.10:2.1": "“Anamataggoyaṁ, bhikkhave, saṁsāro …pe… ",
    "sn15.10:2.2": "ekapuggalassa, bhikkhave, kappaṁ sandhāvato saṁsarato siyā evaṁ mahā aṭṭhikaṅkalo aṭṭhipuñjo aṭṭhirāsi yathāyaṁ vepullo pabbato, sace saṁhārako assa, sambhatañca na vinasseyya. ",
    "sn15.10:2.3": "Taṁ kissa hetu? ",
    "sn15.10:2.4": "Anamataggoyaṁ, bhikkhave, saṁsāro …pe… ",
    "sn15.10:2.5": "alaṁ vimuccitun”ti. ",
    "sn15.10:3.1": "Idamavoca bhagavā. ",
    "sn15.10:3.2": "Idaṁ vatvāna sugato athāparaṁ etadavoca satthā: ",
    "sn15.10:4.1": "“Ekassekena kappena, ",
    "sn15.10:4.2": "puggalassaṭṭhisañcayo; ",
    "sn15.10:4.3": "Siyā pabbatasamo rāsi, ",
    "sn15.10:4.4": "iti vuttaṁ mahesinā. ",
    "sn15.10:5.1": "So kho panāyaṁ akkhāto, ",
    "sn15.10:5.2": "vepullo pabbato mahā; ",
    "sn15.10:5.3": "Uttaro gijjhakūṭassa, ",
    "sn15.10:5.4": "magadhānaṁ giribbaje. ",
    "sn15.10:6.1": "Yato ca ariyasaccāni, ",
    "sn15.10:6.2": "sammappaññāya passati; ",
    "sn15.10:6.3": "Dukkhaṁ dukkhasamuppādaṁ, ",
    "sn15.10:6.4": "dukkhassa ca atikkamaṁ; ",
    "sn15.10:6.5": "Ariyaṁ caṭṭhaṅgikaṁ maggaṁ, ",
    "sn15.10:6.6": "dukkhūpasamagāminaṁ. ",
    "sn15.10:7.1": "Sa sattakkhattuṁparamaṁ, ",
    "sn15.10:7.2": "sandhāvitvāna puggalo; ",
    "sn15.10:7.3": "Dukkhassantakaro hoti, ",
    "sn15.10:7.4": "sabbasaṁyojanakkhayā”ti. ",
    "sn15.10:7.5": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "sn15.10:7.6": "Paṭhamo vaggo. ",
    "sn15.10:8.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn15.10:8.1": "Tiṇakaṭṭhañca pathavī, ",
    "sn15.10:8.2": "assu khīrañca pabbataṁ; ",
    "sn15.10:8.3": "Sāsapā sāvakā gaṅgā, ",
    "sn15.10:8.4": "daṇḍo ca puggalena cāti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn15.10:0.1": "Linked Discourses 15.10 ",
    "sn15.10:0.2": "Chapter One ",
    "sn15.10:0.3": "A Single Individual ",
    "sn15.10:1.1": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. ",
    "sn15.10:1.2": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, ",
    "sn15.10:1.3": "“Mendicants!” ",
    "sn15.10:1.4": "“Venerable sir,” they replied. ",
    "sn15.10:1.5": "The Buddha said this: ",
    "sn15.10:2.1": "“Mendicants, this transmigration has no known beginning. … ",
    "sn15.10:2.2": "One individual roaming and transmigrating for an eon would amass a heap of bones the size of this Mount Vepulla, if they were gathered together and not lost. ",
    "sn15.10:2.3": "Why is that? ",
    "sn15.10:2.4": "This transmigration has no known beginning. … ",
    "sn15.10:2.5": "This is quite enough for you to become disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed regarding all conditions.” ",
    "sn15.10:3.1": "That is what the Buddha said. ",
    "sn15.10:3.2": "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: ",
    "sn15.10:4.1": "“If the bones of a single individual ",
    "sn15.10:4.2": "for a single eon were gathered up, ",
    "sn15.10:4.3": "they’d make a pile the size of a mountain: ",
    "sn15.10:4.4": "so said the great seer. ",
    "sn15.10:5.1": "And this is declared to be ",
    "sn15.10:5.2": "as huge as Mount Vepulla, ",
    "sn15.10:5.3": "higher than the Vulture’s Peak ",
    "sn15.10:5.4": "in the Magadhan mountain range. ",
    "sn15.10:6.1": "But then, with right understanding, ",
    "sn15.10:6.2": "one sees the noble truths—",
    "sn15.10:6.3": "suffering, suffering’s origin, ",
    "sn15.10:6.4": "suffering’s transcendence, ",
    "sn15.10:6.5": "and the noble eightfold path ",
    "sn15.10:6.6": "that leads to the stilling of suffering. ",
    "sn15.10:7.1": "After roaming on seven times at most, ",
    "sn15.10:7.2": "that individual ",
    "sn15.10:7.3": "makes an end of suffering, ",
    "sn15.10:7.4": "with the ending of all fetters.” ",
    "sn15.10:7.5": "",
    "sn15.10:7.6": "",
    "sn15.10:8.1": "",
    "sn15.10:8.2": "",
    "sn15.10:8.3": ""
  },
